This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories as it discusses a multi-task reinforcement learning algorithm that is particularly useful for robotic applications. It also mentions the use of surrogate models and active covariance matrix adaptation, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and neural networks (cs.NE).
